<p><b>What is Revit documentation?</b> Revit is a design and documentation platform that supports the design, drawings, and schedules required for building information modeling (BIM). BIM delivers information about project design, scope, quantities, and phases when you need it.</p>
<p><b>What is the full form of Revit architecture?</b> Solution: The name originates from the phrase "Revise Instantly". The ease of making changes inspired the name Revit, a contraction of Revise-Instantly.</p>
<p><b>Is Revit Architecture different from Revit?</b> Revit allows you to design and document a virtual representation of your project with both parametric 3D modeling and 2D drafting elements. Revit Architecture is an integrated architectural design and documentation environment.</p>
<p><b>What is a BIM Revit file?</b> BIM is the overall process of creating a three-dimensional database in the form of a model of information that pertains to the design of a building. Revit is just one of many software applications under the BIM umbrella that lead to an efficient design of space.</p>